<p>The Philippines accused Chinese maritime forces of firing a water cannon and ramming a Philippine government vessel near Philippine-occupied Thitu (Pag-asa) Island on Sunday, causing minor damage but no injuries [reuters.com#3][abcnews.go.com#5][aljazeera.com#8][dw.com#4]. Beijing rejected the allegation and said the Philippine vessels were &quot;fully responsible&quot; for the collision in disputed waters of the Spratly archipelago [dw.com#4][firstpost.com#7][france24.com#9][thehindu.com#1][japantoday.com#2]. Manila’s coast guard said its ships were anchored as part of a government program to protect local fishermen and vowed to continue operations to safeguard livelihoods [reuters.com#3]. The incident comes amid rising tensions this year around contested areas including Scarborough Shoal, in a sea</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/Jvmyd7l_siJsTpGqY-A6Bc0z6sRHg1fyLRFEhwMYc40eLbCDJ3ucNZm6E06x6Qf4z6Wx9zjCH-M6EYkltczFtNiXRlaGNoYB7gTF6PybOrTKQRnAKastEO7ow7z1zuV4uDyanhAYC-STEMLResnMmBBI_1M6gj7CvFUASKucSQ' alt='Coast guard vessels in the South China Sea amid tensions near Thitu (Pag-asa) Island.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>What happened: Manila says a China coast guard ship used a water cannon and then rammed the BRP Datu Pagbuaya near Thitu Island, causing minor damage but no injuries [reuters.com#3][abcnews.go.com#5][aljazeera.com#8].</li><li>China’s stance: Beijing contends the Philippine vessels bore &quot;full responsibility&quot; for the collision and disputes Manila’s account of the encounter [dw.com#4][firstpost.com#7][france24.com#9][thehindu.com#1][japantoday.com#2].</li><li>Mission purpose: The Philippine vessels, including BRP Datu Pagbuaya, were anchored as part of a government program to protect local fishermen near Pag-asa (Thitu) Island [reuters.com#3].</li><li>Rising tensions: The incident follows months of heightened frictions, including around the prime fishing grounds of Scarborough Shoal [reuters.com#3][thehindu.com#1].</li><li>Strategic stakes: The South China Sea is a vital route for over $3 trillion in annual ship-borne trade and is claimed in parts by several Southeast Asian nations alongside China [reuters.com#3][aljazeera.com#8].</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Philippine Coast Guard: Says Chinese ships used water cannon and rammed a government vessel near Thitu, and vows to continue operations to support fishermen. (<a href='https://www.reuters.com/world/china/philippines-accuses-china-ramming-vessel-near-disputed-island-tensions-soar-2025-10-12/'>Reuters</a>)</li><li>China Coast Guard/Beijing: Asserts the Philippine side bears full responsibility for the collision in the disputed waters. (<a href='https://www.dw.com/en/philippines-says-china-rammed-their-ship-in-south-china-sea/a-74322578'>DW</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/philippines-china-trade-blames-for-vessels-colliding-in-south-china-sea-as-tensions-soar/article70154426.ece'>Philippines, China trade blames for vessels colliding in South China Sea as tensions soar</a> - thehindu.com</li><li><a href='https://japantoday.com/category/world/philippines-china-trade-accusations-over-south-china-sea-vessel-clash'>Philippines, China trade accusations over South China Sea vessel clash</a> - japantoday.com</li><li><a href='https://www.reuters.com/world/china/philippines-accuses-china-ramming-vessel-near-disputed-island-tensions-soar-2025-10-12/'>Philippines accuses China of ramming vessel near disputed island as tensions soar</a> - reuters.com</li><li><a href='https://www.dw.com/en/philippines-says-china-rammed-their-ship-in-south-china-sea/a-74322578'>Philippines says China rammed their ship in South China Sea</a> - dw.com</li><li><a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/chinese-coast-guard-rams-damages-philippine-vessel-off-126443184'>Chinese coast guard rams Philippine vessel off island in South China Sea</a> - abcnews.go.com</li><li><a href='https://www.re